   Here is the 62-37 roll call by which the
Senate on Thursday refused to override President Bush's veto of a
bill protecting Chinese students in the United States.
   Although a majority voted to override, the vote was four short
of the two-thirds necessary.
   A yes vote was to override. Voting yes were 54 Democrats and 8
Republicans. Voting no were 37 Republicans.
